The paper deals with estimating mutual information, which is a fundamental concept in information theory and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the case of discrete-continuous mixtures, which is a common scenario in real-world applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
